      • getPossibleInputSourcePaths

        public Optional<com.google.common.collect.ImmutableSet<SourcePath>> getPossibleInputSourcePaths()
        Description copied from interface: SupportsDependencyFileRuleKey
        Returns a set of all possible source paths that may be returned from SupportsDependencyFileRuleKey.getInputsAfterBuildingLocally(). This information is used by the rule key builder to infer that inputs *not* in this list should be included unconditionally in the rule key. If not present, we treat all the input files as covered by dep file, meaning that they will be included in the rule key only if present in the dep file. TODO(jkeljo): This is only optional because I added it for Java and didn't have the time to go back and figure out how to implement it for C++.
        Specified by:
